<TITLE> CA lauds military's role </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Chittagong, Dec 24(bdnews24.com) - Chief adviser Fakhruddin Ahmed has lauded the armed forces for doing a great job by helping out the civil administration in running the affairs and mainitaining the continuacy of democracy. They have always come forward in times of diaster and other difficult times, said Fakhruddin at a combined parade by army, navy and air forces at Bangladesh Military Academy at Bhatiari in Chittagong on Wednesday. He termed the military as sleepless guards of independence and sovereignty. He pointed out that military academies were set up in the country shortly after independence in 1971 to have skilled armed forces and noted that cadets from friendly countries also learn here. On Wednesday, a total of 182 fresh officers were commissioned to the armed forces. Of them, 133 have been commissioned to the army, 22 to the navy and 27 to the air force. He watched a military exercise as chief guest in presence of the chiefs of three services. bd
